              <p class="text-gray-600">In some cases, yes. Older children who can participate independently may do well with teletherapy only. This decision is made on a case-by-case basis and depends on your child's needs, learning style, and therapy goals. If you are out of range for the in-person service area, you may select teletherapy only!</p>
